{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"homesick-thermal-billygoat","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. On a CI leg where actionlint is not pre-installed (Linux tiers), `make lint` runs\n   `make actionlint-bin`, which downloads `actionlint.tar.gz` from GitHub releases.\n2. The download transiently fails (GitHub network blip); `curl` writes no file.\n3. Observe: the recipe prints `actionlint: installed …` (FALSE SUCCESS) and returns exit 0\n   despite no binary; `make lint` then runs the missing binary → exit 2.\n\n- Expected: a failed/corrupt download aborts `make actionlint-bin` NON-ZERO with a clear\n  error (and transient failures are retried), so CI is reliable and the sha256 gate holds.\n- Actual: the failure is masked as \"installed\" (exit 0), turning a transient blip into a\n  confusing hard CI failure; the pinned-sha256 verification never actually gates.\n\n## Root cause (proven, /rebar-debug)\n\n`actionlint-bin` (Makefile) chains its `curl` download / `sha256sum -c` verify / `tar`\nextract with `;` and ends in an unconditional `echo \"…installed\"`, so any step's failure is\nignored and the recipe returns 0. Deterministically reproduced: a forced 404 → recipe exit 0,\nno binary. Two coupled defects: (1) no `curl` retry (the transient flake trigger); (2) no\n`set -e`/fail-fast (masks the failure and defeats the sha256 gate).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `make actionlint-bin` exits NON-ZERO and installs no binary when the download fails\n      (nonexistent version → HTTP 404). Proving command:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_ci_actionlint_install.py` (RED on the pre-fix recipe).\n- [ ] A successful download still verifies (sha256) and installs the binary (exit 0).\n- [ ] Transient network errors are retried (`curl --retry`).\n- [ ] Fix confined to the `actionlint-bin` recipe (+ the guard test).\n\nObserved: Gerrit-verify run 29619392619, job 88011385914 (py3.12 tier); other tiers passed.","id":"4e99-b2ae-1791-4760","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"CI flake: make actionlint-bin masks a failed download as 'installed' (exit 0) — no fail-fast / no retry"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784331587456234001,"uuid":"98071dd2-3eff-4ffe-8ff7-41ca4ea40c7d"}